gland. (His son Evelyn carried this further — His son Evelyn pursued this claim further."},{"number":5,"category":"family","header":"Sister married Edwards — the Aaron Burr legacy","body":"His sister Sarah Pierpont Edwards married Jonathan Edwards, the Great Awakening theologian. Their daughter Esther married Rev. Aaron Burr Sr., and their son Aaron Burr became the 3rd Vice President of the United States and killed Alexander Hamilton in a duel in 1804. The Pierpont siblings split into two of the most consequential American lineages."}],"education":[{"notes":"Tutor at Yale 1722-1724","school_name":"Yale College","graduation_year":1718,"institution_id":"INST022"}],"bio":{"display_name":"James Pierpont","first_name":"James","last_name":"Pierpont","married_names":[],"bio_blurb":"Yale tutor, then apothecary in Boston and New Haven"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1718"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"Tutor","organization":"Yale College","start_year":1722,"end_year":1724},{"role":"Apothecary","location":"Boston","start_year":1727,"end_year":1754},{"role":"Apothecary","location":"New Haven","start_year":1754,"end_year":1776,"notes":"Occupied his father’s residence at Elm and Temple Streets."}],"slug":"james-pierpont-1699"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}